{
    "cells": [
        {
            "code_hash": "43fe62a87bb3fd4a4680823995f57b2e",
            "console": [],
            "id": "Hbol",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"get-started\">Get started</h1></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "1d0db38904205bec4d6f6f6a1f6cec3e",
            "console": [],
            "id": "MJUe",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "46a1551ea118262b2e1ef35c47c917b9",
            "console": [],
            "id": "vblA",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Let's walk through a small but realistic example. The task is <strong>product review sentiment analysis</strong>: given a customer review, predict whether the sentiment is <code>positive</code>, <code>neutral</code>, or <code>negative</code>, and produce a short justification for the call.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">We start with a tiny labelled dataset. The <code>reference</code> is the ground-truth label.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "fb6ec1e70f2f4b8b3cfff554d8a0fd0f",
            "console": [],
            "id": "bkHC",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "28f16e11b1e5c7ddc099e5a313f79de1",
            "console": [],
            "id": "lEQa",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Now we define the target function — the <strong>thing we actually want to evaluate</strong>. Note that it is not just a thin wrapper around <code>complete()</code>: there can be real pre- and post-processing around the model call. That's intentional. In production, what users hit is rarely the raw completion; it's the completion plus the glue around it. The harness lets us evaluate that full product.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The function must adhere to the <code>TargetFunction</code> protocol: take its <strong>named inputs</strong>, the <strong>prompt template</strong>, and an <strong>LM config</strong>, then return whatever the downstream scorers should consume. The harness unpacks <code>Example.inputs</code> as keyword arguments, so the parameter names must match the dict keys.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The underlying <code>CompletionRequest</code> / <code>CompletionResponse</code> are captured automatically (via <code>lmdk.observe</code>) and attached to the trial — the target doesn't need to surface them.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "66e350c01fa2f0152b1126cda12fb5ce",
            "console": [],
            "id": "PKri",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "c2778f20b1015978c24cc8648c51a891",
            "console": [],
            "id": "Xref",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Now, lets define the moving parts under test. The three sweepable axes are the <strong>prompt template</strong>, the <strong>LM config</strong> (model, generation kwargs, optional output schema), and the target function itself.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "1df45ac73f9346bb68131e956c7b2929",
            "console": [],
            "id": "SFPL",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "6f054a3181b26e6d7f9ae281e313f13e",
            "console": [],
            "id": "BYtC",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">With these ingredients, we can already run a trial: execute the target function on one example with the config under test.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "2f1aca82c7569e5b845a1d92d76e702d",
            "console": [],
            "id": "RGSE",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "application/json": "{\"sentiment\": \"positive\", \"reason\": \"The review expresses strong satisfaction with the product's battery life, screen quality, and overall experience.\"}"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "75c756ef389fe9723278a0d9e5e9d904",
            "console": [],
            "id": "Kclp",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Now that our trial ran successfully, we can jump into quality measurements.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">First, a simple deterministic check: does the predicted label match the ground truth? No LLM judge needed — a <code>ProgrammaticMetric</code> whose scorer follows the <code>ProgrammaticScorer</code> protocol is the right tool. We declare the value space with an <code>Ordinal</code> scale.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "f8623778a6dcf019f876981980e9126c",
            "console": [],
            "id": "emfo",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "ef3970e45eb4402b280bc97145c19646",
            "console": [],
            "id": "Hstk",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Now we score the trial against the metric.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "2a0cdcc23b1e9f45934758a46a534ca3",
            "console": [],
            "id": "nWHF",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "application/vnd.marimo+mimebundle": {
                            "image/png": "data:image/png;base64,",
                            "text/html": "<pre class='text-xs'>Score(raw=True, normalized=1.0, reason=&quot;Predicted &#x27;positive&#x27; matches reference.&quot;)</pre>"
                        }
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "3460227a9d462f573dcd06d91e1d14d2",
            "console": [],
            "id": "iLit",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">The label check is cheap and exact, but it tells us nothing about the <em>reason</em> the model produced — and a good sentiment classifier should be able to justify its call. That's a subjective, open-ended judgement with no ground truth, which is exactly where an LLM judge earns its keep.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">We define an <code>LLMJudgeMetric</code> that grades the quality of the justification. It carries its own <code>LMConfig</code> and judge prompt template. We use the built-in <code>default_llm_judge</code>, which feeds the judge the rendered prompt, the target's output, the reference, and the metric description.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "cfc755dd02c22db29f95cd2850ef6746",
            "console": [],
            "id": "ZHCJ",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "61a315a8965e046279334353d268cb0a",
            "console": [],
            "id": "ROlb",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Let's see what the judge thinks about the system output on our first trial.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "545b6a1e528c0ef0194980a3e57863dd",
            "console": [],
            "id": "qnkX",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "application/vnd.marimo+mimebundle": {
                            "image/png": "data:image/png;base64,",
                            "text/html": "<pre class='text-xs'>Score(raw=&#x27;good&#x27;, normalized=1.0, reason=&quot;The justification provided in the &#x27;reason&#x27; field is grounded in the original review and is coherent with the predicted &#x27;positive&#x27; sentiment label. It cites concrete cues such as &#x27;Battery lasts two full days,&#x27; &#x27;the screen is gorgeous,&#x27; and &#x27;Best phone I&#x27;ve owned,&#x27; which clearly indicate a positive sentiment.&quot;)</pre>"
                        }
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "015faa99c955e30cf6fc16d5c993bc4b",
            "console": [],
            "id": "TqIu",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">Finally, we can wire it all together into an experiment: run <code>classify_sentiment</code> against every example in the dataset and score both metrics on each output.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "dce8c4a7379e6c69b12cd6208eb68bb8",
            "console": [],
            "id": "Vxnm",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/plain": ""
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "0e9ea8d54819eb0fb96580f1f349bd93",
            "console": [],
            "id": "DnEU",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">And a reporting utility renders the results.</span></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "code_hash": "ba62b1d04ab71a0eabf6d5fcf60bbca3",
            "console": [],
            "id": "ulZA",
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"run-report-sentiment-baseline\">Run report: <code>sentiment-baseline</code></h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Summary of one experiment run across the dataset.</span>\n<h2 id=\"experiment\">Experiment</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Model</strong>: <code>mistral:mistral-small-latest</code></li>\n<li><strong>Run timestamp</strong>: 2026-05-19T20:09:52.973112+00:00</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"quality\">Quality</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Mean normalized score across every successful scoring (higher is better, in <code>[0, 1]</code>).</span>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mean normalized score</strong>: 1.0000</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"per-metric-mean-normalized-score\">Per-metric mean normalized score</h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Metric</th>\n<th>Mean normalized</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code>label_correctness</code></td>\n<td>1.0000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>reason_quality</code></td>\n<td>1.0000</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2 id=\"reliability\">Reliability</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Trial failures count against the run (the target is under evaluation); scorer failures are excluded from quality aggregates.</span>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Trials</strong>: 5 successful / 5 total</li>\n<li><strong>Trial failure rate</strong>: 0.00%</li>\n<li><strong>Scorings</strong>: 10 successful / 10 total</li>\n<li><strong>Scoring failure rate</strong>: 0.00%</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"telemetry\">Telemetry</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Averages across successful trials only.</span>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mean latency</strong>: 0.574 s</li>\n<li><strong>Mean output tokens</strong>: 27.0</li>\n<li><strong>Total output tokens</strong>: 135</li>\n</ul></span>"
                    },
                    "type": "data"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
